---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RelatedTools from '../../../components/RelatedTools.astro';

// Tool metadata
const name = "Tuning Fork";
const category = "audio";
const tier = "Audio Utilities";
const description = "Emit stable audio tuning pitches at standard frequencies, calibrate reference pitches, and compare musical intervals.";

// SEO
const pageTitle = "Online Tuning Fork - Free Sound & Pitch Tuner (A440, A432, 128Hz)";
const seoDescription = "Free client-side online tuning fork. Generate precise reference pitches like A440, A432, or 128 hz tuning fork. Learn what is a tuning fork and explore tuning fork therapy for health and healing.";
const canonicalUrl = "https://toolkify.com/tools/audio/tuning-fork";
const ogImage = "/og/tuning-fork.png";
const keywords = "tuning fork, 128 hz tuning fork, tuning fork meaning, tuning fork for health, tuning fork therapy, tuning fork test, tuning fork for healing, what is a tuning fork, tuning fork therapy side effects, tuning fork frequency chart, tuning fork uses medical, how to use a tuning fork, what is a tuning fork used for, 432 hz tuning fork";
---

<Layout 
  title={pageTitle}
  description={seoDescription}
  toolName={name}
  toolCategory={category}
  keywords={keywords}
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="website"
  hideBanner={true}
>
  <!-- FAQ Page JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is a tuning fork?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A tuning fork is a metal acoustic resonator, usually shaped in a two-pronged U-bar. When struck against a surface, it vibrates at a constant, mathematically precise frequency, emitting a pure tone that is widely used for tuning musical instruments, medical testing, and sound therapy.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to use a tuning fork?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To use a physical tuning fork, hold it firmly by the single handle (stem) rather than the prongs. Strike the prongs against a firm but elastic surface (such as a rubber mallet or your knee) to initiate the vibration. You can then hold the vibrating prongs near your ear to listen to the tone, or place the stem base directly on a surface to amplify the resonance.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is a tuning fork used for?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A tuning fork is used for calibrating and tuning musical instruments (like pianos and violins), conducting medical hearing tests (such as the Rinne and Weber tests), diagnosing sensory nerve disorders (like peripheral neuropathy), and facilitating sound therapy/vibrational healing sessions.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How does a tuning fork work?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A tuning fork works by oscillating when struck, creating a physical vibration. Because of its symmetrical design, the two prongs move in opposite directions, canceling out certain kinetic forces at the base and allowing the fork to vibrate at a steady, long-lasting resonant frequency with a clean, sine-wave-like acoustic profile.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Where can I buy a tuning fork?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>You can buy tuning forks from musical instrument retailers, medical supply stores, sound therapy websites, and online marketplaces like Amazon. For digital use, you can access our free, browser-based online tuning fork directly from your computer or smartphone without any installation.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to use a tuning fork for healing?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To use a tuning fork for healing, strike the fork to activate its vibration, then place the flat base of the stem directly onto specific bones, joints, muscles, or acupuncture pressure points on the body. The deep micro-vibrations help relieve physical tension and promote relaxation. You can also hover the prongs near your ears for auditory relaxation.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is tuning fork therapy?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Tuning fork therapy is an alternative sound healing modality that uses the vibrations of calibrated tuning forks to balance the body's energy fields, reduce muscle spasms, alleviate stress, and stimulate blood flow. It is often combined with acupressure, massage therapy, or meditation.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Where to buy a tuning fork?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Tuning forks are available at local music shops, medical supply stores, specialized holistic health outlets, and major online e-commerce platforms. If you do not have a physical fork, you can use our free online tone generator to produce exact standard frequencies.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does tuning fork therapy work?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Yes, many people find tuning fork therapy highly effective for relaxation, stress reduction, and pain management. While clinical studies are continuing to explore the physiological impact of sound vibrations, the therapy has been utilized for decades in sound healing and neuromuscular therapy to induce a deep meditative state.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What does a tuning fork do?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A tuning fork generates a single, stable, and highly accurate reference frequency. It translates physical kinetic energy into a pure acoustic tone and mechanical vibration, which serves as a benchmark for musicians, a diagnostic sensor for medical professionals, and a vibrational healing stimulator for therapists.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <!-- SEO JSON-LD WebApplication Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Tuning Fork & Tone Generator",
      "alternateName": "Client-Side Reference Pitch Generator",
      "url": "https://toolkify.com/tools/audio/tuning-fork",
      "description": "Emit stable, mathematically exact audio pitches using Web Audio. Supports custom calibration from 415Hz to 466Hz, standard presets, and secondary comparison tones.",
      "applicationCategory": "AudioApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires Web Audio API.",
      "featureList": [
        "Mathematically precise tone generation via Web Audio API",
        "Click-free audio envelope start and stop",
        "Standard presets including A440, A432, and C256",
        "Reference pitch calibration between 415Hz and 466Hz",
        "Keyboard shortcuts for play/stop and frequency nudging",
        "Interval comparison mode with secondary tone",
        "Tuning needle gauge and envelope amplitude level visualization"
      ],
      "offers": {
        "@type": "Offer",
        "price": "0.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD"
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- Breadcrumb Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 1,
          "name": "Home",
          "item": "https://toolkify.com/"
        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 2,
          "name": "Audio Tools",
          "item": "https://toolkify.com/tools/audio"
        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          "position": 3,
          "name": "Tuning Fork",
          "item": "https://toolkify.com/tools/audio/tuning-fork"
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <section class="max-w-[1280px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-3 sm:py-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 animate-fade-in-up pb-16 print:p-0">
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 print:hidden">
      <nav
        class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate uppercase"
        aria-label="Breadcrumb"
      >
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Tools</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue capitalize">{category}</span>
      </nav>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between mt-0.5 gap-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight text-primary">
            {name}
          </h1>
          <span class="bg-surface-pricing-featured text-brand-blue text-[10px] py-0.5 px-2 rounded-full font-semibold uppercase whitespace-nowrap shrink-0">
            {tier}
          </span>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <!-- Keyboard shortcuts reference -->
          <button
            type="button"
            id="shortcuts-btn"
            class="hidden sm:inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="View keyboard shortcuts"
          >
            <span>⌨ Keyboard Shortcuts</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="share-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Share tool link"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.684 10.742l5.028-2.513m0 7.544l-5.028-2.513M18 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm-6 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 0a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
            </svg>
            <span>Share</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="how-it-works-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="How Tuning Fork works"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>How it works</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="reset-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-brand-coral hover:border-brand-coral rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Reset inputs and output"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 1121.21 7.89M9 11l3-3 3 3m-3-3v12"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>Reset</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Toast Notification -->
    <div
      id="toast-message"
      class="fixed top-4 right-4 bg-success-accent text-canvas text-xs font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-xl shadow-subtle opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 pointer-events-none z-50"
    >
      Copied!
    </div>

    <!-- Workspace Layout -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-4 items-stretch">
      <!-- Main Controller Panel -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-8 flex flex-col gap-4">
        <!-- Interactive Player Workspace -->
        <div class="card-base flex flex-col gap-4 sm:gap-5 relative overflow-hidden">
          <!-- Tuning Fork decorative ring ripple overlay -->
          <div id="ripple-overlay" class="absolute inset-0 bg-brand-blue/0 pointer-events-none transition-all duration-300"></div>

          <!-- Header status info -->
          <div class="flex justify-between items-center z-10 gap-2 flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-charcoal flex items-center gap-1.5">
              <span id="status-light" class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-slate"></span>
              <span id="status-text" class="truncate max-w-[150px] sm:max-w-none">Audio Context Suspended</span>
            </span>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-1 bg-surface py-0.5 px-2 rounded-full border border-hairline text-[10px] font-mono text-slate">
              <span>A4 Calibrated:</span>
              <span id="ref-pitch-display" class="font-bold text-primary">440.0 Hz</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Display Needle & Visualization Panel -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:flex md:flex-row items-center justify-around gap-2.5 sm:gap-4 bg-surface-soft p-2.5 sm:p-4 rounded-2xl border border-hairline-soft relative z-10">
            
            <!-- Analog Needle Gauge -->
            <div class="col-span-1 flex flex-col items-center gap-1">
              <div class="relative w-28 h-14 sm:w-44 sm:h-22 overflow-hidden flex items-end justify-center">
                <!-- Outer Arc -->
                <svg class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full" viewBox="0 0 100 50">
                  <path d="M 10 50 A 40 40 0 0 1 90 50" fill="none" stroke="#e0e2e8" stroke-width="6" stroke-linecap="round"></path>
                  <path d="M 10 50 A 40 40 0 0 1 90 50" fill="none" stroke="#4262ff" stroke-width="6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="126" stroke-dashoffset="126" id="gauge-progress-arc" class="transition-all duration-500 ease-out"></path>
                  <!-- Dial Ticks -->
                  <line x1="10" y1="50" x2="16" y2="50" stroke="#8e91a0" stroke-width="1"></line>
                  <line x1="50" y1="10" x2="50" y2="16" stroke="#8e91a0" stroke-width="1"></line>
                  <line x1="90" y1="50" x2="84" y2="50" stroke="#8e91a0" stroke-width="1"></line>
                </svg>
                <!-- Needle Element -->
                <div id="gauge-needle" class="absolute bottom-0 w-1 sm:w-1.5 h-9 sm:h-15 bg-primary origin-bottom rounded-t-full transition-transform duration-500 ease-out translate-y-1" style="transform: rotate(0deg);"></div>
                <div class="w-3.5 h-3.5 sm:w-5 sm:h-5 bg-charcoal rounded-full border border-canvas z-10 -mb-2"></div>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between w-26 sm:w-40 text-[8px] sm:text-[9px] font-semibold text-stone uppercase">
                <span>Lower</span>
                <span id="needle-centered-note" class="text-primary font-bold text-[9px] sm:text-[10px]">A4</span>
                <span>Higher</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Animated Tuning Fork Component -->
            <div class="col-span-1 flex flex-col items-center gap-1">
              <div class="relative w-16 h-14 sm:w-24 sm:h-22 flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
                <!-- SVG Tuning Fork -->
                <svg id="tuning-fork-svg" class="w-11 h-13 sm:w-16 sm:h-20 text-stone transition-all duration-300 relative z-10" viewBox="0 0 100 150" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="8" stroke-linecap="round">
                  <!-- Left Prong Group -->
                  <g id="left-prong-group">
                    <path id="left-prong" d="M 30 15 L 30 80" />
                  </g>
                  <!-- Right Prong Group -->
                  <g id="right-prong-group">
                    <path id="right-prong" d="M 70 15 L 70 80" />
                  </g>
                  <!-- U-bend -->
                  <path id="u-bend" d="M 30 80 A 20 20 0 0 0 70 80" />
                  <!-- Base / Stem -->
                  <path d="M 50 100 L 50 135" />
                  <!-- Bottom handle bulb -->
                  <circle cx="50" cy="138" r="8" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
                </svg>
                <!-- Sound waves ripples when playing -->
                <div class="fork-ripple absolute left-[15%] top-[10%] w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-brand-blue/40 opacity-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
                <div class="fork-ripple absolute right-[15%] top-[10%] w-6 h-6 rounded-full border border-brand-blue/40 opacity-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
                <div class="fork-ripple absolute left-[15%] top-[10%] w-10 h-10 rounded-full border border-brand-blue/20 opacity-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
                <div class="fork-ripple absolute right-[15%] top-[10%] w-10 h-10 rounded-full border border-brand-blue/20 opacity-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
              </div>
              <span class="text-[8px] sm:text-[9px] font-bold text-stone uppercase tracking-wider">Resonance</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Digital Readout & Amplitude Level Meter -->
            <div class="col-span-2 md:col-span-1 flex flex-row md:flex-col items-center md:items-start justify-between w-full gap-2 mt-1 md:mt-0 pt-2 md:pt-0 border-t border-hairline-soft md:border-t-0">
              <div class="text-left">
                <span class="text-[8px] sm:text-[10px] font-semibold text-stone uppercase tracking-wider block">Current Frequency</span>
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-0.5 justify-start">
                  <span id="freq-readout" class="font-display font-medium text-2xl sm:text-5xl text-primary tracking-tight">440.00</span>
                  <span class="text-slate font-medium text-xs">Hz</span>
                </div>
                <span id="note-name-readout" class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-semibold text-brand-blue block">Note: A4</span>
              </div>

              <!-- Volume & Envelope Visualizer -->
              <div class="w-32 sm:w-48 flex flex-col gap-0.5">
                <div class="flex justify-between text-[8px] sm:text-[9px] font-semibold text-stone">
                  <span>LEVEL METER</span>
                  <span id="level-percentage">0%</span>
                </div>
                <div class="h-1.5 w-full bg-surface border border-hairline rounded-full overflow-hidden flex items-stretch">
                  <div id="level-bar" class="bg-brand-blue w-0 transition-all duration-75"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Main Player Actions -->
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-2.5 items-center justify-between bg-surface p-2 sm:p-3 rounded-xl border border-hairline z-10">
            <!-- Play and Strike actions -->
            <div class="flex flex-row gap-2 w-full sm:w-auto">
              <!-- Big Toggle Play/Stop -->
              <button
                type="button"
                id="play-stop-btn"
                class="w-1/2 sm:w-auto sm:min-w-[150px] h-9 sm:h-11 bg-primary hover:bg-charcoal text-canvas rounded-full font-bold flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 cursor-pointer transition-all active:scale-95 shadow-md text-xs sm:text-sm select-none"
              >
                <!-- Play icon -->
                <svg id="play-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4 sm:w-5 sm:h-5 fill-current" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"></path>
                </svg>
                <!-- Stop icon (hidden by default) -->
                <svg id="stop-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4 sm:w-5 sm:h-5 fill-current hidden" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path d="M6 6h12v12H6z"></path>
                </svg>
                <span id="play-btn-text">Start Tone</span>
              </button>

              <!-- Strike Fork Button -->
              <button
                type="button"
                id="strike-fork-btn"
                class="w-1/2 sm:w-auto sm:min-w-[150px] h-9 sm:h-11 bg-brand-blue hover:bg-blue-700 text-canvas rounded-full font-bold flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 cursor-pointer transition-all active:scale-95 shadow-md text-xs sm:text-sm select-none"
                title="Strike the tuning fork to play a naturally decaying tone"
              >
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4 sm:w-5 sm:h-5 fill-none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
                </svg>
                <span>Strike Fork</span>
              </button>
            </div>

            <!-- Sound Calibration quick controls -->
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center w-full sm:w-auto justify-end">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                <label for="waveform-select" class="text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate whitespace-nowrap">Waveform</label>
                <select
                  id="waveform-select"
                  class="text-input py-0.5 px-2 text-[11px] h-8 cursor-pointer border border-hairline-strong bg-canvas rounded-full font-medium"
                >
                  <option value="sine" selected>Sine (True Tuning Fork)</option>
                  <option value="triangle">Triangle (Flute tone)</option>
                  <option value="square">Square (Clarinet comparison)</option>
                </select>
              </div>

              <button
                type="button"
                id="btn-share-inline"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-full border border-hairline hover:bg-canvas text-slate hover:text-primary transition-all cursor-pointer"
                title="Copy shareable link for this frequency"
              >
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.684 10.742l4.636-2.318m0 7.152l-4.636-2.318M21 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm-6-8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm0 16a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
                </svg>
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Controls Section Grid -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-2 z-10">
            
            <!-- Left Sub-column: Manual Frequency & Presets -->
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
              <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-xs uppercase text-slate tracking-wider border-b border-hairline-soft pb-1">Hz Controls</h3>
              
              <!-- Manual inputs -->
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="flex-grow flex flex-col gap-1">
                  <label for="freq-input" class="text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate">Manual Frequency (Hz)</label>
                  <input
                    type="number"
                    id="freq-input"
                    class="text-input w-full text-sm font-semibold font-mono"
                    value="440.00"
                    step="0.01"
                    min="20.00"
                    max="5000.00"
                  />
                </div>

                <!-- Increment / Decrement precise buttons -->
                <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
                  <span class="text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate text-center block">Fine Tune</span>
                  <div class="flex rounded-lg border border-hairline overflow-hidden">
                    <button type="button" id="freq-dec-btn" class="px-2.5 h-[44px] bg-canvas hover:bg-surface text-slate border-r border-hairline font-bold text-sm cursor-pointer select-none">-</button>
                    <button type="button" id="freq-inc-btn" class="px-2.5 h-[44px] bg-canvas hover:bg-surface text-slate font-bold text-sm cursor-pointer select-none">+</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Coarse slider container -->
              <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5 mt-1">
                <div class="flex justify-between text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate">
                  <span>Slider Range (20Hz - 2000Hz)</span>
                  <button type="button" id="toggle-fine-drag" class="text-brand-blue hover:underline text-[9px]">Switch to Fine Slider Mode</button>
                </div>
                <input
                  type="range"
                  id="freq-slider"
                  class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                  min="20"
                  max="2000"
                  value="440"
                  step="1"
                />
              </div>

              <!-- Reference Calibrator -->
              <div class="bg-surface-soft p-3.5 rounded-xl border border-hairline flex flex-col gap-2 mt-1">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                  <label for="ref-pitch-slider" class="text-[10px] font-bold text-slate uppercase">A4 Calibrate Reference</label>
                  <button type="button" id="reset-ref-btn" class="text-[9px] text-brand-blue font-semibold hover:underline">Reset to 440Hz</button>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                  <input
                    type="range"
                    id="ref-pitch-slider"
                    class="flex-grow cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                    min="415"
                    max="466"
                    value="440"
